    "created_at": "2017-07-19T21:23:49Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-07-19T21:23:49Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It is not legitimate for server-side application code to raise exceptions into the gRPC Python server-side runtime, and there is no guaranteed behavior of what will happen if server-side application code does fail with an exception. For security reasons we're reluctant to send exception text from server to client.\r\n\r\nIf you'd like your server-side application code to report a problem to your client-side application code, consider using the trailing metadata, status code, and status details facilities? (Unfortunately there's currently a restriction that the status details string must be ASCII; our apologies about that.)"
  },
