    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Do you mean that an rpc handler is not allowed to throw an exception? And if it does, then it's undefined behaviour? Such as the gRPC Python server-side runtime never responds back to the client in this scenario? Certainly a rough edge, but thanks for the details on how to handle this properly with metadata/status/details.\r\n\r\nYou mention the reluctance to send exception text from server to client, but it appears it is currently doing that. It only sends it if its ascii, and raises internally (uncaught) if it's not ascii. This line formats the exception string https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/6613f601660e7cf58db2a5dd1e11556378955910/src/python/grpcio/grpc/_server.py#L380"
  }
